race.description: Integra Insurance Brokers Mandurah Cup Sat Jan 3 Handicap
race.comment: PRINCESS IN RED (5) improved nicely last start when second-up from a spell, closing well but finding one better over this distance at Ascot. Takes on the boys today but with added fitness at the third run back she looks ready to win. MA MA BELLE (9) was ridden with more aggression last time out and turned around some average form with a game win over this track and distance in a Class 1. Meets a better field this time but she likes racing here and with the claim gets in with a similar weight. Worth following. The usually reliable HEZ GOT THE SAFE (2) hasn't landed a blow in two runs this prep. The application of blinkers for the first time might revive his fortunes. RUN PATTIE RUN (3) came with a mighty finish to collect a Class 5 over this distance at Bunbury recently. Very good six-furlong sprinter who can maintain that form at just the third run of the campaign. MANTUA (1) is worth another chance with a couple of gear changes on a nine-day back-up.
